Introduction

To reproduce all panels in this figure you need to download the raw microbiome data deposited in the European Nucleotide Archive (ENA) at EMBL-EBI under accession number PRJEB78503 or alternatively deposit a demand, to the corresponding author, for the âPCNSL.biomâ file (processed microbiome data). In this script the Meta Data is stored in an object named âClinical_datâ.

####Create transformed versions of the data to perform subsequent analyses.

#holmes method
# centered log2-ratio (clr) normalized taxonomic abundances calculated as Aclr=[log2(A1/ga), log2(A2/ga),. log2(An/ga),], where A is a vector of non-zero read counts and ga is the geometric mean of all values of A,

#Convenience functions for geometric mean and clr transform
gm_mean = function(x, na.rm=TRUE){
  # The geometric mean, with some error-protection bits.
  exp(sum(log(x[x > 0 & !is.na(x)]), na.rm=na.rm) / length(x))
}

clr1 = function(x, base=2){
  x <- log((x / gm_mean(x)), base)
  x[!is.finite(x) | is.na(x)] <- 0.0
  return(x)
  }

#set clr function to see if this affects overall results.
clr=clr1

#clr transform data for PCA, multivariate analysis, visualization
ps_clr <- transform_sample_counts(PCNSL_metagenomes2, clr )

#proportion data for visualization
ps_prop <- transform_sample_counts(PCNSL_metagenomes2, function (x) x/sum(x))

#We need the ps_prop, ps_rarefied and er1_subset objects
library(Hmisc)
library(reshape2)
ps_t <- ps_rarefied

ps_t <- ps_clr
ps_t<-prune_samples(rownames(er1_subset), ps_t) ##Subset to needed samples...

# Principal coordinates analysis (PCoA) of the beta diversity 

my_theme2 <- theme(text = element_text(color = "black",  size=14),
        axis.text = element_text(color = "black",  size=12),
        axis.line = element_line(size = 0.6),
        axis.ticks.length  = unit(1, 'mm'),
        axis.ticks = element_line(size = 0.6),
        axis.text.x = element_text(vjust=0.5),
        plot.title = element_text(size=12),
        plot.subtitle = element_text(size=8))

#features with low abundance (<0.01%) were all excluded from the analysis.
ps_t <- ps_prop
ps_t<-prune_samples(rownames(er1_subset), ps_t) ##Subset to needed samples...

###Filter...>0.01% (this is to keep....)
threshould<-1
tmp<-ps_t@otu_table[,]
tmp<-apply(tmp, 1, function(x){names(table(x>0.0001))[table(x>0.0001)>threshould]})
tmp<-unlist(tmp);tmp<-tmp[tmp==TRUE]
tmp<-names(tmp)
###Filter does 

library(vegan)
cts_fil<-as.data.frame(t(ps_t@otu_table))
mt<-cts_fil[,colnames(cts_fil)%in%tmp]

# dist_ <- vegdist(cts_fil, method = 'bray')
# eigen <- pcoa(dist_)$values$Eigenvalues
# percent_var <- signif(eigen/sum(eigen), 3)*100
# 
# bc <- cmdscale(dist_, k = 2)

###Method=canberra

distance <- vegan::vegdist(mt, method = 'canberra')

meta_sub_MM <- er1[rownames(mt),]
pcoa <- cmdscale(distance, k = (nrow(mt) - 1), eig = TRUE)
plot_data <- data.frame({pcoa$point})[1:2]
plot_data$Sample_name <- rownames(plot_data)
names(plot_data)[1:2] <- c('PCoA1', 'PCoA2')
eig = pcoa$eig
plot_data$Antibiotics_intake_brief <- meta_sub_MM[rownames(plot_data),"Antibiotics_intake_brief"]
plot_data$Antibiotics_intake_brief2 <- meta_sub_MM[rownames(plot_data),"Antibiotics_intake_brief2"]

##Calculate ANOSIM to annotate...
library("vegan")
packageVersion("vegan")
#using rarefied data for this testing
set.seed(10)
ps_t2 <- ps_rarefied
ps_t2<-prune_samples(rownames(er1_subset), ps_t2) #
mtx_group = get_variable(ps_t2, "Antibiotics_intake_brief")
mtx_ano = anosim(phyloseq::distance(ps_t2, "bray"), mtx_group)
mtx_ano

###Beta dispersion....
print("beta dispersion testing")
###
ps_perma_bray <- phyloseq::distance(ps_t2, method = "bray")

# make a data frame from the sample_data
sampledf <- data.frame(sample_data(ps_t2))

beta <- betadisper(ps_perma_bray, sampledf$Antibiotics_intake_brief)
beta<-permutest(beta) #tests whether differences are due to group dispersions (if they are, then p will be significant)


# adonis test, equivalent to PERMANOCA
###To test the significance of between-sample diversity alternation, permutational analysis of variance (PERMANOVA) was performed with the adonis function within the R (v. 3.6.2) package vegan (v.2.5-6)
adonis_tmp<-vegan::adonis(distance ~ Antibiotics_intake_brief, meta_sub_MM, permutations = 9999) 
adonis_tmp$aov.tab ##Significant....


options(repr.plot.width = 6, repr.plot.height = 4)

  my_theme2+scale_color_manual(values = c(NO="black", YES="#E71D36"),labels=c("NO","YES"))+
  labs(title = paste0('PCOA of Antibiotics intake \nR = ',round(mtx_ano$statistic,2),"\np= ",round(mtx_ano$signif,3),"\nBeta dispersion pval=",round(beta$tab$`Pr(>F)`[1],3)))
